26/11/2003
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The UN war crimes court in The Hague starts a two-day hearing in the case of General Radislav Krstic, who was sentenced to 46 years in prison in August 2001 after being convicted of genocide in connection with the 1995 Srebrenica massacre. 
The defence is seeking a lesser sentence, while the prosecution wants life imprisonment for the former Bosnian Serb commander.(PBS, AFP - 26/11/03)
